Highlights of Beijing-based Newspapers
BEIJING , November 15 ( Xinhua ) -- Highlights of today 's major Beijing-based newspapers :
" People 's Daily "
-- Li Ruihuan , chairman of the Chinese People 's Political Consultative Conference ( CPPCC ) National Committee , has expressed satisfaction with the smooth development of Sino-Spanish relations .
During his talks yesterday with Juan Ignacio Barrero , president of the Spanish Senate , Li said that since China and Spain forged diplomatic ties 25 years ago , the two countries have maintained good relations featuring frequent high-level visits , expanded two-way trade , and enhanced exchanges in the scientific , technological and cultural spheres .
-- The King of Cambodia Norodom Sihanouk and Queen Norodom Monineath Sihanouk arrived in Beijing yesterday afternoon for a routine health examination .
" Xinhua Daily Telegraph "
-- President Jiang Zemin 's upcoming Russia visit is of great significance for strengthening Russian-Chinese ties and forming a new international pattern .
This remark was made by Igor Rogachev , Russian ambassador to China , during an interview with Xinhua on Saturday .
The ambassador said the anticipated talks between the two top leaders will be the sixth between them , and will continue the frank dialogue which began with Russian President Boris Yeltsin 's China visit in 1992 , and the discussions will push forward bilateral ties including two-way trade .
-- Scientists from China and abroad will conduct joint observations of the upcoming meteor storm in the Constellation Leo , which will occur from 2 - 4 a.m. on November 18 .
The Constellation Leo Meteor Storm takes places once every 33 years on the average , and the upcoming one will be the first visible in the eastern hemisphere in a century .
